Appendix D: Phase 1 Implementation Plan & X-Hab Deliverables

D.1 Detailed 12-Month Work Breakdown Structure (WBS)

· Month 1-3: Foundation
  · Task 1.1: Finalize system requirements document.
  · Task 1.2: Complete literature review and assumptions document (Appendix C).
  · Task 1.3: Set up ASPEN Plus model framework.
· Month 4-6: Core Process Analysis
  · Task 2.1: Execute thermodynamic & kinetic parameter sweep.
  · Task 2.2: Develop initial reactor geometry for CFD.
  · Task 2.3: Commence pFMEA workshops.
· Month 7-9: Integration & AI Development
  · Task 3.1: Run CFD and thermal-structural analysis.
  · Task 3.2: Generate synthetic data sets from models.
  · Task 3.3: Begin AI algorithm development and training.
· Month 10-12: Validation & Reporting
  · Task 4.1: Execute integrated Digital Twin simulation.
  · Task 4.2: Finalize pFMEA and risk matrix.
  · Task 4.3: Compile Final Feasibility Report and Phase 2 Plan.

D.2 Specific X-Hab 2026 Deliverables

1. A Final Feasibility Report containing all analysis from Appendices A-C.
2. A Digital Twin Software Package: A functional, documented software suite containing the SIL simulation of the CHRSy-AI system, demonstrating the AI control architecture.
3. A Preliminary Design Package: CAD models of the reactor core and CCC, material analysis reports, and interface control documents for major subsystems.
4. A Phase 2 Prototype Development Plan: A detailed proposal for building and testing a sub-scale, heated reactor core, including success metrics, test procedures, and a budget estimate.

